Reasoning: The paper deals with finding structural similarities in graph data, which is a task in data mining and knowledge discovery. The paper also mentions the use of Formal Concept Analysis, which is a subfield of data mining. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DM (Data Mining). The paper also deals with mappings and permutations, which are topics in computational complexity and algorithms, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) likely sub-categories as well. The investigation of clone items is related to pattern recognition and machine learning, making cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the experimental investigation of real-world data involves statistical analysis and modeling, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible sub-category as well.
